			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: haste! omg help<a name="36645"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 27 04 4:26 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Unchayned, maybe you should take similar advice and delete your worthless comment...
<br />

<br />
Battle cry of the vah shir is a special type of haste song, most commonly called overhaste (or haste v3).  Basically, this haste stacks with item haste and &quot;normal&quot; spell/song haste, and will go over the haste cap.
<br />

<br />
Now to answer your question, it depends on what/who you have with you.  If you have an enchanter hasting you, then there's no need to play Vilia's Chorus of Celerity (just using this song as an example), because the enchanter has better haste and they don't stack.  In that case, all you have to play is battle cry of the vah shir (giving everybody 15% more haste, even if they are already at the haste cap from item + chanty haste).
<br />

<br />
However, if you don't have anyone casting haste on you, or if the person casting haste doesn't give as much haste as your song (beastlord haste for example), then you should twist both Vilia's Chorus of Celerity and Battle cry of the vah shir (one to provide &quot;normal&quot; haste, and the other to provide overhaste).</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
