				<td colspan="2"><span>I think Unchayned is getting <a target="_new" href="http://www.eqdiva.com/EQ/Song.aspx?s=2606&amp;c=1&amp;ForumID=80">battlecry of the vahshir</a> and <a target="_new" href="http://www.eqdiva.com/EQ/Song.aspx?s=1449&amp;c=1&amp;ForumID=75">melody of ervaj</a> confused.  Ervaj requires brass and is a 5% haste, Battlecry does not and is 15% (v3).
<br />

<br />
Before PoP and the troubador mace the average bard at level 50 would have to bag weapons and use a brass instrument for Ervaj.  Thus, while the other members of the group would gain a small dps boost, it often would not compensate for the loss of the melee dps from the bard.  This is where the dream group for ervaj line of thinking comes from.
<br />

<br />
Since battlecry has no brass restriction (the brass mod has no effect) a bard can continue to add melee dps while boosting group melee dps by at least 7%.  Battlecry will be in most group twist lineups until it's replaced by warsong of the vah shir.</span></td>
